2025 May 21

1 Preparations

Load libraries and general settings:

## load libraries
library(tidyverse)
library(afex)
library(emmeans)
library(effectsize)
library(ggpubr)
library(psychr) # remotes::install_github("haiyangjin/psychr")
emm_options(lmer.df = "Satterthwaite") # as pre-registered

two_colors <- c("#D55E00", "#56B4E9") # facilitation and interference
sig_color <- "red"
dark_colors <- c("#800D00", "#165F83", "gray45") # darker (facilitation, interference, null)

dir_lmm <- "hpc_lmm"
dir_lmm_cue <- "hpc_lmm_cue"
dir_fig <- "figure"
ylimit_cf_d <- c(-.5, 3.6)
ylimit_cf_fi_d <- c(-1.1, 1.1)
ylimit_cf_rt <- c(650, 1150)
ylimit_cf_fi_rt <- c(-100, 100)

# APA theme for figures
theme_set(papaja::theme_apa(base_size = 12, base_family = "Helvetica", box = FALSE))
theme_update(strip.placement = "outside")

1.1 Experiment 1

df_E1a_raw <- readxl::read_excel(file.path("data", "Exp1a_eye_raw_data.xlsx")) %>% 
  filter(Procedure != "PracProc") %>% 
  transmute(SubjCode = as_factor(sprintf("11%02d", Subject)),
            Age,
            Sex = as.factor(Sex),
            Feature = "eye",
            State = str_remove(ExperimentName, "Hard") %>% tolower(),
            State = factor(State, levels = c("open", "close")),
            State = fct_recode(State, open = "open", closed = "close"),
            Location = as.factor(Location),
            Acc = TrialSlide.ACC,
            RT = TrialSlide.RT,
            isabove200 = as.integer(RT > 200))

2 Experiment 1

2.1 Experiment 1a

Eyes

df_E1a_clean <- df_E1a_raw %>% 
  filter(isabove200 == 1) %>% 
  select(-isabove200)

2.1.1 Accuracy

df_E1a_acc <- df_E1a_clean %>% 
  group_by(SubjCode, Feature, State) %>% 
  summarize(Acc = mean(Acc),
            .groups = "drop")
df_E1a_acc
df_E1a_acc_wide <- df_E1a_acc %>% 
  pivot_wider(id_cols = SubjCode,
              names_from = State,
              values_from = Acc)
df_E1a_acc_wide

2.1.1.1 t-test

t_E1a_acc <- t.test(df_E1a_acc_wide$open,
                    df_E1a_acc_wide$closed,
                    paired = TRUE,
                    var.equal = TRUE)
t_E1a_acc
## 
##  Paired t-test
## 
## data:  df_E1a_acc_wide$open and df_E1a_acc_wide$closed
## t = 3.151, df = 19, p-value = 0.00526
## alternative hypothesis: true mean difference is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.00425155 0.02107283
## sample estimates:
## mean difference 
##      0.01266219
# effect size
repeated_measures_d(t_E1a_acc)

2.1.1.2 RM-ANOVA

Whether the performance varies across the four locations:

aov_E1a_acc <- aov_ez(id = "SubjCode",
                      dv = "Acc",
                      within = c("State", "Location"),
                      data = df_E1a_clean,
                      fun_aggregate = mean)
aov_E1a_acc
## Anova Table (Type 3 tests)
## 
## Response: Acc
##           Effect          df  MSE        F  ges p.value
## 1          State       1, 19 0.00 10.05 ** .041    .005
## 2       Location 2.45, 46.53 0.00     2.15 .042    .118
## 3 State:Location 2.29, 43.59 0.00     0.53 .008    .618
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '+' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Sphericity correction method: GG
